translation:
May tranquility, self-control, austerity, purity, contentment, forbearance, magnanimity, enthusiasm, steadfastness, sovereignty, and power be established. 
For the brahmana is characterized by faith, truthfulness, and worship of Brahma; 
for the kshatriya, by courage, strength, and valor; 
for the vaishya, by uprightness, charity, and pursuit of wealth; 
and for the shudra, by serving the brahmanas, cows, and gods without deceit. Upon obtaining this, let there be contentment.
